===(Trailblazer), do you know...===
{{Messages|text=
:'''Jade:''' (Trailblazer), do you know anything about "managing up"?
:'''Jade:''' I heard it's a really popular concept among younger professionals
:{Choice} I know all about "managing up"!
::'''(Trailblazer):''' I know all about "managing up"!
::'''(Trailblazer):''' If work is overwhelming you, reach out to your manager and pass some their way. If it isn't, pass some their way anyway!
::'''Jade:''' That's a unique way to look at it
:{Choice} Heard of it, but it's unrealistic
::'''(Trailblazer):''' Mm-hmm. "If work is overwhelming you, reach out to your manager and pass some their way. If it isn't, pass some their way anyway," right?
::'''(Trailblazer):''' But I think it's unrealistic. Constantly clashing with your manager is a surefire way to get fired, isn't it
::'''Jade:''' It looks like you have a good understanding of it
:'''Jade:''' The young employees at the IPC have been talking about it, and their views have reached my ears
:'''Jade:''' Sentiments toward "managing up" largely depend on their supervisor's management style
:'''Jade:''' "Director Topaz may be a woman of swift and decisive action, but she listens to advice where she should."
:'''Jade:''' "Director Aventurine has a sharp eye for everything. Putting the initial 'whys' and 'hows' aside, if he says something can be done, then it will get done."
:{Choice} What about Madam Jade's style?
:'''(Trailblazer):''' What about Madam Jade's style?
:'''Jade:''' Take a guess?
:{Choice} Can't tell
:'''(Trailblazer):''' Can't tell... I've got a feeling that nobody can "managing up" with you
:'''Jade:''' Hmm... Or maybe it's the exact opposite
:'''Jade:''' The world of youths is a vibrant and dynamic one. The new generation inevitably surpasses the old
:'''Jade:''' But before that happens, as one who walks before them, I'll help them become the best versions of themselves
:{Choice} The IPC are all workaholics!
::'''(Trailblazer):''' So this is the reason behind the workaholic culture at the IPC
::'''Jade:''' Diligence and fortitude are the keys to growth
::'''Jade:''' Not everyone gets the opportunity to climb higher
:{Choice} The Ten Stonehearts self-improve too?
::'''(Trailblazer):''' Do the Ten Stonehearts need to polish themselves too?
::'''Jade:''' Absolutely. Chiselling the Cornerstones is just the beginning
::'''Jade:''' Only by steadily tempering our hearts and building unbreakable walls can we broaden our horizons
:'''Jade:''' From what I've seen, (Trailblazer), you're a rare and unique gem
:'''Jade:''' If you're interested, why not come to the IPC and experience for yourself our uncompromising dedication to polishing oneself?
}}
